# Code conventions ŌĆö ConciergeTravel.fr

## Layering
- Pure domain logic lives in `packages/domain/`. No `next/`, `@supabase/*`, `fetch`, `Date.now()` allowed there.
- Vendor calls live in `packages/integrations/`. Each vendor has a dedicated package or sub-folder.
- Apps (`apps/web`, `apps/admin`) compose domain + integrations. They never re-implement domain rules.

## TypeScript strict
- No `any`, no `as Foo`, no `!` non-null assertion. Narrow with type guards or Zod.
- Branded types for IDs and slugs.
- Discriminated unions for state and `Result<T, Error>` for fallible operations.
- Exhaustive switch with a `never`-returning helper.

## Naming
- Files: kebab-case (`hotel-detail.tsx`, `cancellation-policy.ts`). React components export PascalCase.
- Symbols: PascalCase types/components, camelCase values, SCREAMING_SNAKE for env-only constants.
- Test files alongside source: `<name>.test.ts(x)`.

## Imports
- Use path aliases (`@cct/domain`, `@cct/integrations`, `@cct/seo`, ŌĆ”) instead of deep relative paths.
- Group: built-ins ŌåÆ external ŌåÆ workspace ŌåÆ relative. Prettier organises automatically; do not fight it.
- Never import server-only secrets in client components. ESLint enforces.

## Comments
- Only when intent is non-obvious. Do not narrate the code.
- ADR-level decisions reference the ADR number in a comment, e.g. `// see docs/adr/0003-payload-cms.md`.

## React / Next.js
- Server Components by default. `'use client'` only for genuine interactivity.
- Server Actions: validate input with Zod at the boundary; return discriminated `Result` unions.
- Avoid `useEffect` for data fetching ŌĆö use Server Components or actions.

## Validation
- Vendor responses parsed by Zod schemas in `packages/integrations/<vendor>/types.ts`. Cast results never bypass parse.

## Errors
- Domain returns typed errors. Throwing reserved for programmer assertions.
- HTTP route handlers and server actions translate domain errors to user-facing responses without leaking stack traces.

## Tests
- New business rule ŌåÆ unit test in `packages/domain/`.
- New integration function ŌåÆ MSW-mocked test in the integration package.
- New user journey impacting booking, search, account, or comparator ŌåÆ Playwright E2E case.

## Security
- Read secrets only from validated env via `@cct/config/env`.
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` outside of trusted JSON-LD scripts.
- Do not log PII (email, phone, full address).
